ell%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EKelsey%20Birch%20remembers%20the%20crushing%20pressure%2C%20the%20sharp%20jerks%2C%20and%20the%20feeling%20of%20hands%20inside%20her%20abdomen.%20%26quot%3BI%20felt%20like%20I%20was%20being%20torn%20apart%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20couldn't%20handle%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBirch%2C%20a%20then%2028-year-old%20emergency%20dispatcher%20in%20Colorado%2C%20hadn't%20gone%20into%20labor%20expecting%20surgery.%20She%20was%20healthy.%20Her%20first%20pregnancy%20had%20been%20going%20well%2C%20and%20her%20full-term%20baby%20was%20positioned%20face%20down%20%E2%80%94%20an%20ideal%20candidate%20for%20a%20vaginal%20birth.%20As%20her%20contractions%20grew%20stronger%2C%20a%20delivery%20room%20nurse%20urged%20Birch%20to%20get%20an%20epidural%20before%20the%20hospital%20anesthesiologist%20finished%20his%20shift.%20Birch%20agreed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20American%20College%20of%20Obstetricians%20and%20Gynecologists%20recommends%20that%20a%20woman%20with%20an%20epidural%20in%20first-time%20labor%20push%20for%20up%20to%20four%20hours.%20Birch%20pushed%20for%20just%20over%20two%20before%20a%20doctor%20intervened.%20Her%20labor%20had%20failed%20to%20progress%2C%20her%20medical%20records%20noted%2C%20so%2C%20like%20one%20in%20three%20American%20women%20who%20give%20birth%2C%20Birch%20underwent%20a%20cesarean%20section.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20half-hour%20surgery%20began%20months%20of%20recovery.%20For%20weeks%2C%20Birch%20struggled%20to%20hold%20and%20breastfeed%20her%20newborn%20daughter.%20Her%20incision%20site%20was%20searingly%20painful%3B%20first%20as%20a%20fresh%20wound%20and%20again%20as%20it%20healed%2C%20scar%20tissue%20adhering%20to%20skin%20and%20muscle.%20Like%20many%20women%20who%20undergo%20a%20C-section%2C%20she%20learned%20to%20cope%20with%20intrusive%20memories%20of%20the%20surgery.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EC-sections%20are%20now%20the%20most%20common%20inpatient%20surgery%20in%20America.%20Business%20Insider%20analyzed%20years%20of%20hospital%20delivery%20data%20from%20Florida%2C%20Mississippi%2C%20and%20Iowa%20and%20found%20that%20C-section%20rates%20can%20differ%20sharply%20between%20hospitals%20just%20miles%20apart%20%E2%80%94%20even%20when%20caring%20for%20similar%2C%20low-risk%20patients.%20Those%20gaps%2C%20experts%20say%2C%20point%20to%20how%20a%20hospital's%20policies%2C%20culture%2C%20and%20financial%20incentives%20can%20push%20surgery%20rates%20higher%2C%20helping%20explain%20why%20the%20US%20consistently%20performs%20far%20more%20C-sections%20than%20global%20health%20authorities%20consider%20necessary.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%201970%2C%20just%20over%205%25%20of%20babies%20in%20the%20US%20were%20delivered%20by%20C-section%20nationwide%20%E2%80%94%20too%20low%20to%20protect%20some%20women%20and%20their%20babies.%20That%20rate%20tripled%20within%20a%20decade.%20Now%2C%20for%20nearly%2020%20years%2C%20over%2030%25%20of%20babies%20in%20the%20United%20States%20have%20been%20born%20by%20C-section%2C%20around%20double%20the%20rate%20the%20World%20Health%20Organization%20says%20is%20%26quot%3Bideal%26quot%3B%20for%20maternal%20and%20infant%20health.%20US%20doctors%20perform%20these%20surgeries%2060%25%20more%20frequently%20than%20doctors%20in%20France%2C%20and%20nearly%20double%20the%20rate%20of%20Finland%20and%20Sweden.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20of%20them%2C%20maternal%20health%20experts%20told%20Business%20Insider%2C%20are%20medically%20unnecessary.%20Federal%20health%20agencies%20consider%20women%20with%20low-risk%20pregnancies%20%E2%80%94%20those%20who%20are%20pregnant%20for%20the%20first%20time%2C%20are%20at%20full%20term%2C%20are%20not%20delivering%20twins%2C%20and%20whose%20babies%20are%20head-down%20rather%20than%20breech%20%E2%80%94%20the%20least%20likely%20group%20to%20require%20surgery%20to%20safely%20deliver%20their%20babies.%20Yet%20more%20than%20a%20quarter%20of%20those%20women%20delivered%20by%20C-section%20in%20the%20US%20in%202023%2C%20the%20most%20recently%20available%20year%20with%20national%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FCemwg%2Fembed.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22feedlyNoScript%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Line%20chart%20showing%20U.S.%20national%20C-section%20rates%20from%201970%20to%202023.%20The%20rate%20for%20all%20C-sections%20rises%20steadily%20from%20around%205.5%25%20in%201970%20to%2032.4%25%20in%202023.%20A%20second%20line%2C%20representing%20low-risk%20C-section%20rates%2C%20begins%20in%201990%20at%2021.6%25%20and%20follows%20a%20similar%20pattern%2C%20reaching%2026.6%25%20in%202023.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FCemwg%2Ffull.png%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20large%20study%20estimates%20that%20as%20many%20as%2019%25%20of%20all%20births%20should%20be%20C-sections%20to%20protect%20women%20and%20their%20babies%2C%20leaving%20as%20many%20as%2013%25%20possibly%20performed%20needlessly%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20suggests%20roughly%20one%20in%2010%20pregnant%20American%20women%20%E2%80%94%20nearly%20half%20a%20million%20women%20each%20year%20%E2%80%94%20are%20operated%20on%20unnecessarily%2C%20undergoing%20major%20abdominal%20surgeries%20that%20carry%20a%20higher%20risk%20of%20hemorrhage%2C%20blood%20clots%2C%20and%20infection%2C%20and%20leave%20women%20more%20likely%20to%20develop%20dangerous%20complications%20in%20their%20future%20pregnancies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20because%20women%20are%20asking%20for%20more%20C-sections.%20Only%20an%20estimated%202.5%25%20of%20US%20babies%20are%20born%20by%20elective%20C-section%20each%20year.%20Instead%2C%20experts%20say%2C%20the%20reason%20behind%20the%20high%20C-section%20rate%20largely%20comes%20down%20to%20the%20structure%20of%20the%20American%20medical%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EC-sections%20are%20more%20profitable%2C%20predictable%2C%20and%20are%20perceived%20to%20be%20more%20protective%20against%20lawsuits%20than%20vaginal%20births%2C%20according%20to%20experts%20and%20multiple%20studies.%20They%20say%20health%20systems%20looking%20to%20keep%20operating%20rooms%20full%2C%20revenue%20up%2C%20and%20liability%20risk%20minimized%20are%20indirectly%20incentivized%20to%20keep%20surgery%20rates%20high.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPut%20plainly%2C%20a%20high%20C-section%20rate%20may%20just%20be%20better%20for%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228fac84de-1b8e-40f5-ae9d-8157840c6947%5C%22%3EWhen%20C-sections%20hurt%20more%20than%20they%20help%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EC-sections%20are%20often%20critical%2C%20sometimes%20lifesaving%20procedures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20medical%20emergencies%2C%20like%20when%20the%20placenta%20completely%20blocks%20the%20cervix%20or%20an%20umbilical%20cord%20slips%20down%20past%20the%20baby%2C%20a%20C-section%20is%20mandatory.%20Failure%20to%20promptly%20perform%20the%20surgery%20can%20disable%20or%20kill%20the%20woman%2C%20her%20baby%2C%20or%20both.%20Other%20factors%20%E2%80%94%20including%20a%20pregnant%20woman's%20age%2C%20whether%20she's%20obese%2C%20or%20if%20she's%20diagnosed%20with%20diabetes%20or%20pre-eclampsia%20%E2%80%94%20all%20increase%20the%20chance%20that%20a%20C-section%20is%20the%20safest%20way%20to%20deliver%20a%20baby.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20deliver%20a%20baby%20by%20C-section%2C%20a%20surgeon%20dissects%20through%20seven%20layers%20of%20body%20tissue%3A%20skin%2C%20fat%2C%20fascia%2C%20muscle%2C%20peritoneum%2C%20uterus%2C%20and%20amniotic%20sac.%20Doctors%20first%20use%20a%20scalpel%3B%20later%2C%20they%20may%20use%20their%20fingers%20or%20a%20blunt%20tool.%20Like%20any%20abdominal%20surgery%2C%20it%20also%20presents%20immediate%20risks%2C%20including%20infections%2C%20hemorrhages%2C%20blood%20clots%2C%20or%20injury%20to%20other%20organs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20risks%20increase%20with%20additional%20C-sections%2C%20and%20a%20woman%20is%20far%20more%20likely%20to%20have%20another%20C-section%20once%20she's%20had%20her%20first.%20In%202021%2C%2086%25%20of%20women%20who%20previously%20had%20a%20C-section%20underwent%20the%20surgery%20again%20to%20deliver%20their%20next%20baby.%20While%20studies%20show%20that%20as%20many%20as%2080%25%20of%20women%20who%20have%20undergone%20a%20prior%20C-section%20can%20safely%20deliver%20their%20next%20baby%20vaginally%2C%20many%20hospitals%20nationwide%20ban%20women%20who%20have%20had%20a%20C-section%20from%20attempting%20a%20later%20vaginal%20birth%2C%20citing%20safety%20and%20liability%20concerns.%20Each%20additional%20surgery%20will%20increase%20her%20risk%20of%20developing%20severe%20complications%2C%20like%20placenta%20accreta%2C%20which%20almost%20always%20requires%20a%20hysterectomy%20to%20prevent%20hemorrhaging.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20complications%20can%20sometimes%20turn%20deadly.%20While%20rare%2C%20the%20United%20States%20has%20the%20highest%20rate%20of%20maternal%20mortality%20among%20high-income%20countries%20%E2%80%94%2018.6%20deaths%20per%20100%2C000%20live%20births%20in%202023%20%E2%80%94%20and%20a%20woman%20who%20receives%20a%20C-section%20is%20up%20to%20five%20times%20more%20likely%20to%20die%20due%20to%20pregnancy-related%20causes%20than%20a%20woman%20who%20delivers%20vaginally.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20when%20the%20surgery%20goes%20as%20expected%2C%20some%20women%20describe%20the%20experience%20as%20extreme%2C%20even%20traumatic.%20Women%20are%20anesthetized%2C%20but%20most%20choose%20to%20remain%20conscious%20to%20witness%20the%20birth%20of%20their%20child.%20While%20some%20women%20who%20spoke%20with%20Business%20Insider%20said%20their%20surgeries%20were%20unremarkable%20and%20felt%20little%20of%20the%20procedure%2C%20others%20told%20Business%20Insider%20they%20still%20felt%20the%20snagging%20pull%20of%20the%20scalpel%2C%20intense%20pressure%2C%20and%20sometimes%20shocking%20pain.%20Their%20memories%20of%20the%20surgery%20are%20punctuated%20with%20specific%20detail%3A%20their%20arms%20held%20outstretched%2C%20pinned%20in%20restraints%20secured%20to%20the%20operating%20table%3B%20their%20bodies%20trembling%3B%20and%20their%20newborns%20held%20amid%20IV%20lines%20and%20the%20surgical%20drape.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226720%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22two%20surgeons%20performing%20a%20c%20section%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68a89b22cfc04e97619bdd19%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224480%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EEdgar%20Barragan%20Juarez%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20a%20C-section%2C%20some%20women%20endure%20weeks%20or%20months%20of%20painful%20recovery%2C%20much%20longer%20than%20women%20who%20deliver%20vaginally.%20Women%20told%20Business%20Insider%20they%20struggled%20to%20breastfeed%2C%20shower%2C%20and%20get%20out%20of%20bed%20to%20care%20for%20their%20newborns.%20Some%20suffered%20painful%20infections%20along%20their%204-%20to%206-inch%20surgical%20incisions.%20Others%20weathered%20panic%20attacks%2C%20nightmares%2C%20and%20lingering%20anxiety.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22add7f122-7894-40b6-8fd0-1833459a1231%5C%22%3EThe%20hospital%20you%20choose%20can%20affect%20how%20likely%20you%20are%20to%20get%20a%20C-section%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDoctors%20delivering%20babies%20have%20to%20make%20tough%20calls.%20If%20a%20fetal%20heart%20rate%20monitor%20alerts%20that%20a%20baby%20is%20in%20distress%2C%20or%20if%20a%20woman's%20labor%20is%20so%20prolonged%20that%20she%20or%20her%20baby%20is%20at%20risk%20of%20suffering%20severe%20injury%2C%20a%20doctor%20might%20feel%20compelled%20to%20intervene.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20if%20the%20medical%20necessity%20of%20C-section%20is%20ambiguous%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20can't%20really%20gamble%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Dr.%20Elizabeth%20Langen%2C%20an%20OB-GYN%20and%20a%20clinical%20associate%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Michigan%20who%20studies%20C-section%20rates.%20Doctors%20may%20choose%20to%20perform%20a%20C-section%20because%20%26quot%3Bit's%20devastating%20when%20a%20baby%20is%20born%20and%20isn't%20doing%20well%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou%20keep%20thinking%2C%20'Is%20there%20something%20else%20I%20could%20have%20done%3F'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20health%20and%20safety%20of%20a%20woman%20and%20her%20baby%20aren't%20always%20the%20only%20influences%20at%20play.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EControlling%20for%20a%20constellation%20of%20factors%20%E2%80%94%20hospital%20obstetric%20care%20levels%2C%20delivery%20volume%2C%20urban%20or%20rural%20location%2C%20maternal%20age%2C%20race%2C%20health%2C%20and%20income%20%E2%80%94%20multiple%20studies%20show%20that%20one%20of%20the%20strongest%20predictors%20of%20whether%20a%20woman%20will%20get%20a%20C-section%20is%20which%20hospital%20she%20delivers%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20requested%20data%20on%20hospital%20delivery%20data%20from%20all%2050%20states%20and%20DC%2C%20and%20analyzed%20data%20from%20three%20states%20that%20responded%20first%20to%20the%20request%20or%20had%20already%20published%20the%20data%20publicly%3A%20Florida%2C%20Mississippi%2C%20and%20Iowa.%20Business%20Insider's%20analysis%20reveals%20huge%20variations%20in%20C-section%20rates%20from%20one%20neighboring%20hospital%20to%20another%20%E2%80%94%20suggesting%20a%20woman's%20chance%20of%20undergoing%20a%20C-section%20is%20affected%20by%20her%20choice%20between%20two%20close-by%20hospitals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2Frjyip%2Fembed.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22feedlyNoScript%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Chart%20showing%20range%20of%20C-section%20rates%20for%20hospitals%20within%20Florida%2C%20Iowa%2C%20and%20Mississippi.%20In%20Florida%2C%20rates%20range%20from%2021.7%25%20to%2057.6%25%3B%20in%20Iowa%2C%20from%2016.8%25%20to%2041.8%25%3B%20and%20in%20Mississippi%2C%20from%2024.4%25%20to%2051.4%25.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2Frjyip%2Ffull.png%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EA%2015-minute%20drive%20is%20enough%20to%20swing%20outcomes.%20In%202019%2C%20the%20average%20rate%20of%20C-sections%20at%20one%20Palm%20Beach%20County%20hospital%20in%20Florida%20was%2026%25%20higher%20than%20at%20a%20hospital%20less%20than%205%20miles%20away%20in%20a%20similarly%20majority%20white%2C%20wealthy%20area.%20Between%202010%20and%202019%2C%20Business%20Insider%20found%20similar%20instances%20in%20Broward%2C%20Duval%2C%20Miami-Dade%2C%20and%20at%20least%20five%20other%20Florida%20counties.%20The%20hospitals%20all%20had%20similar%20levels%20of%20obstetric%20care%20and%20numbers%20of%20babies%20delivered.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESimilar%20patterns%20were%20found%20in%20Mississippi%2C%20where%20C-section%20rates%20are%20among%20the%20highest%20in%20the%20country%2C%20as%20well%20as%20in%20Iowa%2C%20where%20C-section%20rates%20are%20among%20the%20lowest%20nationwide.%20Doctors%20at%20a%20hospital%20in%20northwest%20Iowa%2C%20performed%20surgeries%20on%20women%20who%20were%20pregnant%20for%20the%20first%20time%20at%20a%20rate%2065%25%20higher%20than%20doctors%20at%20a%20comparable%20hospital%2015%20minutes%20away%2C%20according%20to%20Business%20Insider's%20analysis%20of%20aggregate%20five-year%20hospital%20birth%20data%20from%202019%20to%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20C-sections%20performed%20on%20low-risk%20pregnancies%2C%20differences%20in%20hospital%20rates%20may%20be%20more%20telling%2C%20experts%20told%20Business%20Insider%2C%20as%20surgeries%20performed%20in%20this%20category%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20have%20been%20medically%20unnecessary.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Mississippi%2C%20which%20has%20the%20highest%20rate%20of%20C-sections%20on%20low-risk%20pregnancies%20in%20the%20country%2C%20some%20hospitals%20had%20low-risk%20pregnancy%20cesarean%20delivery%20rates%20that%20swung%20as%20low%20as%2014%25.%20Doctors%20at%20other%20hospitals%20performed%20C-sections%20on%2045%25%20of%20all%20women%20with%20low-risk%20pregnancies%2C%20according%20to%20the%20analysis%20of%20data%20from%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHow%20a%20hospital%20operates%20%E2%80%94%20its%20workplace%20culture%2C%20administrators'%20priorities%2C%20and%20the%20type%20and%20number%20of%20staff%20employed%2C%20particularly%20nurses%20or%20midwives%20%E2%80%94%20can%20dramatically%20impact%20how%20many%20cesarean%20deliveries%20its%20doctors%20perform%2C%20said%20Dr.%20Emily%20White%20VanGompel%2C%20a%20family%20medicine%20doctor%20and%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Illinois%20Chicago%20who%20studies%20how%20organizations%20impact%20C-section%20rates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHospital%20administrators%20and%20care%20staff%20can%20foster%20cultures%20more%20supportive%20of%20vaginal%20birth%2C%20White%20VanGompel%20said.%20Conversely%2C%20they%20can%20also%20implement%20policies%20and%20care%20standards%20that%20cause%20doctors%20to%20intervene%20more%20in%20a%20woman's%20labor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20hospitals%20that%20treat%20women%20with%20high-risk%20pregnancies%20may%20require%20a%20high%20C-section%20rate%20to%20most%20safely%20deliver%20their%20patients'%20babies.%20A%20risk-adverse%20hospital%20may%20also%20lead%20doctors%20to%20perform%20more%20medical%20interventions%20in%20part%20to%20minimize%20its%20risk%20of%20a%20lawsuit%2C%20said%20Louise%20Roth%2C%20a%20sociology%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Arizona%20who%20studies%20how%20organizations%20and%20medical%20malpractice%20influence%20maternal%20health%2C%20including%20C-section%20rates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDoctors%20may%20then%20practice%20medicine%20in%20ways%20that%20evidence-based%20studies%20show%20can%20increase%20the%20chance%20of%20a%20C-section%3A%20induce%20labor%20more%20often%2C%20continuously%20monitor%20more%20fetal%20heart%20rates%20in%20low-risk%20pregnancies%2C%20and%20interrupt%20women%20who%20push%20for%20more%20than%20a%20few%20hours%20%E2%80%94%20all%20procedures%20that%20are%20more%20insulating%20in%20the%20case%20of%20a%20lawsuit%2C%20Roth%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOB-GYNs%20are%20among%20the%20doctors%20most%20likely%20to%20face%20a%20legal%20threat%20at%20least%20once%20in%20their%20career%2C%20a%202023%20study%20found%2C%20and%20a%20lawsuit%20filed%20over%20the%20serious%20harm%20or%20death%20of%20a%20baby%20can%20result%20in%20tens%20of%20millions%20of%20dollars%20in%20jury%20awards.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20often%20will%20teach%20young%20obstetricians%20that%20you%20don't%20get%20sued%20for%20doing%20a%20C-section%2C%20you%20get%20sued%20for%20not%20doing%20a%20C-section%2C%26quot%3B%20Langen%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERoth%20said%20doing%20more%20also%20satisfies%20another%20hospital%20demand%3A%20billing%20more%20procedures%20and%20garnering%20more%20reimbursements.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIntervening%20more%20almost%20always%20means%20a%20C-section%2C%26quot%3B%20Roth%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BBut%20less%20intervention%20means%20less%20money.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Kelsey%20Birch's%20case%2C%20the%20hospital%20where%20she%20delivered%20disclosed%20in%20a%202025%20survey%20that%20it%20had%20an%20average%20C-section%20rate%2022%25%20higher%20than%20the%20state%20average.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2226e7c424-ef68-45f2-b48d-92327852a056%5C%22%3EWhy%20the%20US%20performs%20so%20many%20C-sections%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20C-section%20is%20major%20surgery.%20It's%20also%20lucrative.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProviders%20in%20the%201970s%20and%201980s%20responded%20to%20%26quot%3Bmarket%20shocks%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20dips%20in%20the%20birthrate%20that%20undercut%20their%20profits%20%E2%80%94%20by%20performing%20more%20highly%20reimbursed%20C-sections%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jstor.org%2Fstable%2F2555794%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epioneering%201996%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20found.%20A%202017%20study%20revealed%20that%20California%20women%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20were%2012%25%20more%20likely%20to%20receive%20a%20C-section%20if%20their%20doctor%20was%20reimbursed%20just%20%24420%20more%20for%20the%20surgery%20than%20for%20a%20vaginal%20delivery.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20average%2C%20US%20insurers%20in%202020%20paid%20%2417%2C103%20for%20a%20C-section%20and%20%2411%2C453%20for%20vaginal%20birth%2C%20according%20to%20one%202022%20study.%20Physicians%20were%20paid%20about%2016%25%20more%2C%20on%20average%2C%20for%20a%20C-section%20than%20a%20vaginal%20delivery%2C%20according%20to%20a%202015%20study.%20Because%20a%20C-section%20takes%20much%20less%20time%2C%20it's%20more%20cost-effective%20for%20both%20providers%20and%20hospitals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2Fut0QX%2Fembed.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22feedlyNoScript%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Map%20of%20the%20United%20States%20showing%20C-section%20rates%20for%20low-risk%20pregnancies%20by%20county.%20The%20data%20reveal%20regional%20variations%2C%20with%20rates%20generally%20highest%20across%20the%20South%2C%20while%20lower%20rates%20are%20more%20common%20out%20West.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2Fut0QX%2Ffull.png%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20researchers%20in%20the%20early%202000s%20found%20that%20pregnant%20women%20who%20are%20older%2C%20obese%2C%20or%20who%20have%20other%20preexisting%20health%20issues%20undergo%20C-sections%20at%20higher%20rates%2C%20more%20recent%20studies%20have%20since%20found%20that%20controlling%20for%20these%20and%20many%20other%20patient%20factors%20doesn't%20eliminate%20the%20wide%20swings%20in%20C-section%20rates%20between%20hospitals%20or%20explain%20the%20high%20C-section%20rate%20nationwide.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResearch%20has%20repeatedly%20shown%20the%20connection%20between%20profits%20and%20surgical%20deliveries.%20Women%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Farticles%2FPMC5318567%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewho%20gave%20birth%20at%20for-profit%20hospitals%3C%2Fa%3E%20were%20more%20likely%20to%20deliver%20by%20C-section%3B%20women%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2F33739430%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emore%20likely%20to%20undergo%20a%20C-section%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20hospitals%20that%20reap%20higher%20profits%20from%20each%20C-section%20than%20hospitals%20where%20the%20procedure%20is%20less%20lucrative%3B%20and%20Florida%20obstetricians%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubsonline.informs.org%2Fdoi%2F10.1287%2Fmnsc.2022.4571%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eincreased%20the%20number%20of%20C-sections%3C%2Fa%3E%20they%20performed%20after%20their%20practices%20were%20acquired%20by%20management%20companies%20that%20prioritized%20increasing%20practice%20revenue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20women%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20get%20the%20surgery.%20Black%20women%20nationwide%20undergo%20C-sections%20at%20higher%20rates%20than%20white%20women.%20Doctors%20in%20hospitals%20across%20New%20Jersey%2C%20for%20example%2C%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nber.org%2Fpapers%2Fw32891%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emuch%20more%20likely%20to%20give%3C%2Fa%3E%20Black%20women%20unnecessary%20C-sections%20to%20fill%20empty%20operating%20rooms%20and%20maximize%20payouts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDirectly%20incentivizing%20doctors%20to%20perform%20more%20C-sections%20is%20illegal%2C%20but%20other%20incentives%20like%20bonus%20payments%20for%20bringing%20in%20more%20money%20to%20the%20practice%20or%20mandatory%20practice%20revenue%20thresholds%20can%20influence%20doctors%20to%20increase%20the%20number%20of%20surgeries%20they%20perform%2C%20said%20Ambar%20La%20Forgia%2C%20an%20associate%20professor%20at%20Haas%20School%20of%20Business%20at%20the%20University%20of%20California%2C%20Berkley%2C%20and%20the%20author%20of%20the%20Florida%20study.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20known%20fact%20that%20C-sections%20reimburse%20more%20highly%20than%20a%20vaginal%20birth%2C%20but%20they're%20also%20easier%20to%20do%20and%20easier%20to%20schedule%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20La%20Forgia%2C%20making%20them%20attractive%20procedures%20to%20healthcare%20companies%20looking%20to%20boost%20their%20bottom%20line.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20some%20cases%2C%20overuse%20becomes%20criminal.%20In%20January%202025%2C%20the%20Department%20of%20Justice%20accused%20Chesapeake%20Regional%20Medical%20Center%20in%20Southeast%20Virginia%20of%20fraudulently%20billing%20for%20unnecessary%20procedures%2C%20including%20C-sections%20tied%20to%20the%20hospital's%20former%20chief%20obstetrician%2C%20Javaid%20Perwaiz.%20Prosecutors%20said%20Perwaiz%20routinely%20falsified%20records%20to%20justify%20early%20labor%20inductions%20and%20C-sections%20timed%20to%20his%20weekend%20surgery%20block.%20The%20pattern%20was%20so%20blatant%20that%20hospital%20staff%20nicknamed%20the%20resulting%20NICU%20admissions%20the%20%26quot%3BPerwaiz%20special%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20a%20federal%20indictment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20indictment%20called%20the%20fraud%20%26quot%3Bpatently%20obvious%26quot%3B%20and%20an%20%26quot%3Bopen%20secret%26quot%3B%20that%20was%20documented%20repeatedly%20to%20hospital%20leadership%20and%20ignored.%20The%20hospital%20turned%20a%20blind%20eye%2C%20the%20indictment%20said%2C%20because%20Perwaiz's%20actions%20reaped%20a%20financial%20reward.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20hospital%20had%20been%20aware%20of%20red%20flags%20around%20Perwaiz's%20history%20for%20decades%2C%20the%20indictment%20charged.%20Following%20Perwaiz's%20federal%20tax%20fraud%20conviction%20in%201996%2C%20another%20obstetrician%20at%20Chesapeake%20Regional%20warned%20the%20Virginia%20medical%20board%20that%20%26quot%3Bunnecessary%20gynecologic%20surgery%20is%20a%20growth%20industry%20in%20Chesapeake%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20the%20indictment%2C%20and%20that%20Perwaiz%20might%20be%20incentivized%20to%20perform%20even%20more%20surgeries%20to%20pay%20off%20his%20fraud%20debts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAround%20the%20same%20time%2C%20the%20indictment%20charged%2C%20Chesapeake%20Regional's%20president%20wrote%20a%20letter%20to%20the%20medical%20board%20supporting%20the%20reinstatement%20of%20Perwaiz's%20medical%20license%2C%20citing%20his%20value%20to%20the%20hospital's%20bottom%20line.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223900%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22external%20photo%20of%20the%20office%20of%20javaid%20perwaiz%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68a89aad194a2d49b8af045c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222600%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Chesapeake%2C%20Virginia%20offices%20where%20Dr.%20Javaid%20Perwaiz%20used%20to%20work%20out%20of.%3Cp%3EThe%20Washington%20Post%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EPerwaiz%20was%20charged%20in%20a%20separate%20criminal%20case%20in%202019%20and%20convicted%20in%202021%20for%20performing%20medically%20unnecessary%20surgeries%2C%20including%20C-sections.%20He%20was%20sentenced%20to%2059%20years%20in%20prison.%20His%20lawyers%20declined%20to%20comment%20on%20Business%20Insider's%20reporting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDr.%20Nick%20Oberheiden%2C%20Chesapeake%20Regional's%20attorney%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20the%20hospital%20denied%20any%20wrongdoing.%20%26quot%3BWe%20are%20confident%20that%20the%20court%20and%20a%20jury%20will%20find%2C%20based%20on%20the%20facts%2C%20the%20law%2C%20and%20the%20evidence%2C%20that%20Dr.%20Perwaiz%20was%20the%20sole%20wrongdoer%2C%26quot%3B%20Oberheiden%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20case%20against%20Chesapeake%20Regional%20is%20ongoing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22376e4592-d85d-438a-adda-a3cf1f6d196b%5C%22%3EC-section%20rates%20can%20be%20lowered%20%E2%80%94%20if%20hospitals%20and%20states%20make%20it%20a%20priority%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20C-section%20rate%20at%20each%20individual%20hospital%20isn't%20an%20intractable%20problem%2C%20said%20White%20VanGompel%2C%20the%20family%20medicine%20doctor.%20Since%20hospital%20policies%2C%20administration%20priorities%2C%20and%20staff%20culture%20have%20so%20much%20bearing%20on%20increasing%20C-section%20rates%2C%20she%20told%20Business%20Insider%2C%20changing%20policy%2C%20priorities%2C%20and%20culture%20can%20also%20lower%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%202024%20study%2C%20White%20VanGompel%20and%20co-authors%20studied%20hospitals%20in%20California%20and%20Florida%20that%20focused%20on%20safely%20lowering%20their%20C-section%20rate%20and%20managed%20to%20reduce%20cesarean%20births%20by%205%25%20for%20at%20least%2018%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20found%20the%20most%20successful%20hospitals%20had%20strong%20leadership%20support%2C%20communication%20between%20care%20teams%20supportive%20of%20vaginal%20delivery%2C%20and%20a%20culture%20that%20empowered%20nurses%20to%20advocate%20for%20their%20patients%20without%20retribution.%20(Nationwide%2C%20hospitals%20with%20more%20nursing%20staff%20or%20that%20employ%20midwives%20are%20also%20associated%20with%20lower%20C-section%20rates.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECalifornia%20also%20shows%20what's%20possible%20at%20the%20state%20level.%20In%202015%2C%20the%20California%20Maternal%20Quality%20Care%20Collaborative%20launched%20a%20campaign%20with%20policy%20recommendations%2C%20financial%20incentives%2C%20and%20new%20public%20transparency%20requirements%20%E2%80%94%20including%20publicly%20publishing%20all%20hospitals'%20annual%20low-risk%20C-section%20rates%20%E2%80%94%20aimed%20at%20lowering%20low-risk%20pregnancy%20C-section%20rates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202014%2C%20California's%20low-risk%20pregnancy%20C-section%20rate%20mirrored%20the%20country's%20nationwide%3A%2026%25.%20Five%20years%20later%2C%20the%20rate%20had%20declined%20to%2022.8%25%20%E2%80%94%20a%2012%25%20drop.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStates%20like%20Wisconsin%2C%20Illinois%2C%20and%20New%20Jersey%20have%20also%20seen%20success%20with%20initiatives%20meant%20to%20lower%20C-section%20rates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20kinds%20of%20state%20policies%20and%20hospital-level%20interventions%20aren't%20just%20niceties%2C%20only%20implemented%20when%20it's%20convenient%20for%20providers%20and%20hospitals%2C%20White%20VanGompel%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWomen's%20health%20is%20at%20stake%2C%20White%20VanGompel%20said.%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20what%20actually%20gets%20results.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBack%20in%20Colorado%2C%20Kelsey%20Birch%20wrote%20a%20complaint%20letter%20to%20the%20administrator%20of%20the%20hospital%20where%20she%20gave%20birth.%20%26quot%3BI%20now%20have%20a%20scar%20on%20my%20uterus%2C%20which%20could%20affect%20any%20subsequent%20pregnancies%20and%20births%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20wrote.%20She%20feared%20her%20providers%20had%20rushed%20her%20first%20with%20the%20epidural%2C%20and%20then%20again%20as%20she%20attempted%20to%20give%20birth%20vaginally.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20believe%20my%20cesarean%20could%20have%20been%20avoided.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHave%20a%20tip%3F%20Contact%20Hannah%20Beckler%20via%20email%20at%20hbeckler%40businessinsider.com%20or%20Signal%20at%20hbeckler.72.%20Use%20a%20personal%20email%20address%20and%20a%20nonwork%20device%3B%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finsider-guide-to-securely-sharing-whistleblower-information-about-powerful-institutions-2021-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Ehere's%20our%20guide%20to%20sharing%20information%20securely.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fc-sections-hospitals-profit-business-cost-2025-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1755940441000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68913948f748d8c055f6de3a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fc-sections-hospitals-profit-business-cost-2025-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20hospital%20you%20choose%20can%20affect%20how%20likely%20you%20are%20to%20get%20a%20C-section%20%E2%80%94%20and%20experts%20say%20profit%20is%20one%20reason.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22hbeckler%40insider.com%20(Hannah%20Beckler)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fc-sections-hospitals-profit-business-cost-2025-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20bought%20my%20college%20son%20a%20townhome%20instead%20of%20wasting%20%2412%2C000%20a%20year%20on%20his%20student%20housing.%20I%20might%20even%20make%20a%20profit.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22964%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20headshot%20of%20a%20woman.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68a8c305194a2d49b8af0c23%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221306%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELeAnne%20Carswell%20didn't%20want%20to%20waste%20money%20on%20her%20son's%20rent%2C%20so%20she%20bought%20him%20a%20home.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20LeAnne%20Carswell%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EA%20college%20mom%20bought%20a%20townhome%20for%20her%20son%20to%20save%20on%20student%20housing%20costs.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShe%20thought%20paying%20upward%20of%20%2412%2C000%20a%20year%20for%20housing%20was%20a%20waste%20of%20money.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShe%20expects%20to%20profit%2C%20or%20at%20least%20break%20even%2C%20when%20she%20decides%20to%20sell.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20conversations%20with%20LeAnne%20Carswell%2C%2051%2C%20a%20real%20estate%20agent%20in%20South%20Carolina%20who%20decided%20to%20buy%20a%20home%20for%20her%20son%20to%20live%20in%20while%20studying%20at%20Clemson%20University%20instead%20of%20paying%20his%20rent.%20The%20conversation%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20son%20started%20at%20a%20sister%20school%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fphotos-clemsons-football-facility-2017-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EClemson%20University%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20his%20freshman%20year.%20So%20he%20did%20his%20first%20year%20at%20that%20tech%20school%2C%20and%20then%20Clemson%20took%20him%20in%20as%20a%20sophomore%20this%20year%2C%20but%20he%20lived%20on%20Clemson's%20campus.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fplanned-sons-college-dorm-room-with-moms-roommates-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edorm%20with%20three%20roommates%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20don't%20remember%20how%20much%20room%20and%20board%20was%2C%20but%20I%20know%20it%20was%20a%20waste%20of%20money%20because%20we%20were%20just%20throwing%20it%20away.%20%3Cem%3E%5BEditor's%20note%3A%20According%20to%20Clemson%20University%2C%20estimated%20housing%20costs%20for%20the%202025-2026%20school%20year%20are%20%248%2C904.%5D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20came%20to%20me%20last%20fall%20and%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BWe've%20got%20to%20start%20finding%20where%20I'm%20going%20to%20live%20in%20the%20fall%20of%202025.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20thought%20that%20was%20so%20far%20away%2C%20but%20he%20said%20everybody's%20going%20and%20looking.%20So%20all%20three%20of%20his%20roommates%20went%20and%20looked%20at%20a%20new%20high-rise%20near%20Clemson%20that's%20the%20trendy%20place%20to%20go.%20It%20was%20between%20%241%2C000%20and%20%241%2C200%20a%20month%20%E2%80%94%20and%20he'd%20still%20have%20other%20roommates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BI'm%20not%20paying%20that.%26quot%3B%20So%20we%20started%20searching%20around%20for%20somewhere%20to%20buy%20rather%20than%20just%20wasting%20that%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20heard%20of%20other%20people%20owning%20properties%20while%20their%20kids%20were%20at%20school.%20I%20actually%20just%20got%20finished%20selling%20a%20home%20where%20the%20parents%20of%20a%20senior%20at%20Anderson%20University%20had%20owned%20it%2C%20and%20she%20had%20rented%20out%20three%20or%20four%20rooms.%20In%20that%20particular%20situation%2C%20she%20made%20a%20little%20bit%20of%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2251245ccd-ca59-4e7c-9659-b1067da205c5%5C%22%3EI%20expect%20to%20at%20least%20make%20my%20money%20back%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAbout%2010%20minutes%20from%20Clemson%20is%20a%20little%20city%20called%20Pendleton%2C%20South%20Carolina.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20were%20some%20new%20townhomes%20being%20built%20there.%20A%20Clemson%20soccer%20coach%20had%20gotten%20a%20new%20job%20somewhere%20in%20Texas%20and%20was%20leaving%20after%20having%20only%20owned%20the%20townhome%20for%20five%20months%20%E2%80%94%20she%20even%20had%20it%20all%20furnished.%20She%20bought%20it%20for%20%24225%2C000%2C%20and%20we%20bought%20it%20from%20her%20for%20%24227%2C000%20in%20cash%2C%20fully%20furnished.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20has%20three%20bedrooms%2C%20two-and-a-half%20bathrooms%2C%20a%20one-car%20garage%2C%20and%201%2C523%20square%20feet.%20All%20three%20bedrooms%20and%20a%20laundry%20room%20are%20upstairs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22640%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20exterior%20of%20a%20townhome%20in%20South%20Carolina.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68a89f27a17a8c5b4053531f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22480%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20exterior%20of%20the%20townhome.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20LeAnne%20Carswell.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20closed%20at%20the%20end%20of%20February%2C%20so%20it%20sat%20there%20for%20a%20while.%20School%20was%20still%20going%20on%2C%20so%20for%20a%20month%2C%20my%20son%20went%20back%20and%20forth%20between%20his%20place%20in%20Clemson%20and%20the%20townhome.%20And%20then%20he%20came%20home%20for%20two%20months%2C%20and%20we%20just%20left%20it%20vacant.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20friends%20went%20off%20and%20rented%20the%20trendy%20%241%2C000%20to%20%241%2C200%20a%20month%20unit%20somewhere%20else%20%E2%80%94%20even%20though%20I%20told%20him%20to%20tell%20them%20we're%20buying%20something%20and%20to%20not%20do%20anything%20yet.%20But%20they%20all%20were%20scared%20they%20were%20going%20to%20be%20homeless.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMe%20being%20in%20real%20estate%2C%20I%20just%20kind%20of%20knew%20what%20was%20going%20on%20in%20the%20market.%20I%20thought%2C%20%26quot%3BWe're%20going%20to%20slow%20walk%20this.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20did%20end%20up%20renting%20one%20room%20to%20a%20kid%20my%20son%20went%20to%20high%20school%20with%20who's%20going%20to%20Clemson%20for%20%24775%20a%20month.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20there's%20the%20smaller%20bedroom%2C%20which%20we%20hadn't%20done%20anything%20with%20this%20year.%20I%20don't%20know%20if%20we%20would%20be%20able%20to%20rent%20it%20out%20this%20semester.%20Maybe%20in%20the%20spring%20that%20would%20be%20something%20that%20they%20could%20do%2C%20but%20I%20don't%20know%20that%20I%20would%20get%20as%20much%20because%20it's%20the%20smallest%20of%20the%20rooms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20don't%20know%20what%20I'm%20going%20to%20do%20with%20the%20townhome%20once%20he%20graduates.%20I've%20got%20a%20sister%20who's%20got%20two%20boys%2C%20so%20maybe%20I'll%20sell%20it%20to%20her%2C%20but%20we'll%20see%20what%20happens.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20expect%20to%20profit%20or%20at%20least%20break%20even%20once%20I%20sell%20it.%20I%20wasn't%20looking%20to%20lose%20%2412%2C000%20a%20year%20for%20the%20next%20three%20or%20four%20years%20%E2%80%94%20who%20knows%20how%20long%20it's%20going%20to%20take%20him%20to%20get%20through%20school%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDo%20you%20have%20a%20story%20to%20share%20about%20buying%20property%20for%20your%20college-age%20children%3F%20Contact%20this%20reporter%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Ajpandy%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Ejpandy%40