didn't%20change%20during%20his%20time%20on%20the%20team%2C%20he%20said%20they%20are%20now%20working%20in%20an%20individual%20contributor%20role.%20He%20also%20said%20he%20saw%20the%20number%20of%20reports%20per%20manager%20increase%20on%20other%20teams.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20saw%20managers%20leave%20and%20other%20managers%20absorb%20that%20head%20count%2C%20so%20you%20go%20from%20managing%2010%20people%20to%20now%20maybe%2018%20people%2C%20which%20when%20you%20talk%20to%20those%20managers%2C%20becomes%20really%20hard%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20great%20flattening%20was%20definitely%20happening.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeyond%20layoffs%20and%20shifts%20in%20management%20structure%2C%20Coachman%20said%20he%20also%20began%20being%20asked%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eto%20focus%20more%20on%20performance%20metrics%2C%20which%20he%20felt%20came%20at%20the%20cost%20of%20flexibility%20and%20meaningful%20customer%20work.%20In%20recent%20years%2C%20Big%20Tech%20firms%2C%20including%20Microsoft%2C%20Google%2C%20Meta%2C%20and%20Amazon%2C%20have%20revamped%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftech-giants-overhaul-pay-rewarding-stars-scrutinizing-underachievers-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eperformance%20review%20and%20compensation%20structures%C2%A0%3C%2Fa%3Eto%20better%20reward%20top%20performers%20and%20weed%20out%20underperformers%20in%20pursuit%20of%C2%A0smaller%2C%20higher-performing%20teams.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20key%20factor%20in%20his%20decision%20to%20resign%20was%20the%20uptick%20in%20business%20travel.%20He%20said%20he%20was%20on%20the%20road%20about%20three%20times%20a%20month%20%E2%80%94%20a%20return%20to%20pre-pandemic%20norms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20just%20got%20to%20a%20point%20where%20I%20was%20missing%20too%20much%20of%20my%20kids'%20lives%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20his%20work%20frustrations%20made%20travel%20less%20tolerable.%C2%A0%26quot%3BIt%20was%20different%20when%20I%20was%20traveling%20and%20the%20job%20was%20awesome.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220e94b6b7-98c9-4b73-a0fb-6d22a13545f8%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ETaking%20the%20risk%20of%20resigning%20without%20a%20new%20job%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Coachman%20started%20his%20job%20search%20in%20July%202024%2C%20he%20thought%20it%20was%20going%20to%20be%20fairly%20easy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20seemed%20to%20be%20plenty%20of%20job%20postings%20on%20platforms%20like%20LinkedIn%20and%20Indeed%2C%20so%20after%20pinpointing%20a%20few%20roles%20he%20felt%20qualified%20for%2C%20he%20figured%20he'd%20be%20able%20to%20get%20interviews%20and%20eventually%20land%20an%20offer.%20But%20he%20quickly%20realized%20it%20wouldn't%20be%20that%20simple.%20After%20all%2C%20US%20businesses%20were%20hiring%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flaid-off-accenture-manager-struggles-salary-expectations-tough-job-market-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Enearly%20the%20slowest%20pace%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20more%20than%20a%20decade.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20was%20six%20months%20of%20basically%20just%20being%20ghosted%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20a%20completely%20different%20world%20than%20when%20I%20had%20applied%20to%20a%20job%20decades%20ago.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECoachman%20said%20he%20went%20through%20several%20rounds%20of%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20tweaks%20%E2%80%94%20thinking%20the%20format%20might%20be%20the%20issue%20%E2%80%94%20but%20still%20got%20little%20response.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20his%20job%20search%20dragged%20on%2C%20Coachman%20said%20he%20was%20hesitant%20to%20resign%20from%20his%20Microsoft%20job%20before%20having%20another%20role%20lined%20up%20because%20it%20would%20mean%20giving%20up%20a%20steady%20paycheck%20and%20unvested%20company%20stock.%20However%2C%20he%20said%20the%20%26quot%3Brainy%20day%20fund%26quot%3B%20he'd%20built%20over%20the%20years%20helped%20him%20feel%20more%20comfortable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20had%20enough%20savings%20that%20even%20if%20it%20would%20take%20me%20a%20year%20to%20find%20a%20job%2C%20I%20would%20be%20fine%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20it%20was%20just%20getting%20the%20courage%20to%20take%20that%20jump.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20early%202024%2C%20Coachman%20said%20he%20hired%20a%20life%20coach%20%E2%80%94%20in%20part%20to%20help%20him%20navigate%20the%20changes%20he%20was%20experiencing%20at%20work.%20He%20said%20the%20life%20coach%20helped%20him%20get%20confident%20in%20his%20decision%20to%20resign%2C%20adding%20that%20hiring%20them%20was%20maybe%20the%20%26quot%3Bbest%20investment%26quot%3B%20he'd%20ever%20made.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22cc40d1b9-9987-421d-ae3a-6773aa8aebf6%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHis%20network%20made%20the%20difference%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20resigning%2C%20Coachman%20said%20he%20adjusted%20his%20job%20search%20strategy.%20Rather%20than%20simply%20applying%20for%20jobs%2C%20he%20spent%20more%20time%20tapping%20into%20the%20network%20he'd%20built%20over%20the%20years.%20He%20targeted%20roles%20at%20companies%20where%20he%20knew%20someone%2C%20then%20reached%20out%20to%20ask%20whether%20they%20thought%20he'd%20be%20a%20good%20fit%20%E2%80%94%20and%20if%20they'd%20be%20willing%20to%20refer%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20one%20instance%2C%20he%20saw%20a%20few%20open%20roles%20at%20the%20data%20analytics%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhen-ai-automation-replacing-humans-databricks-ceo-ali-ghodsi-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAI%20startup%20Databricks%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20where%20a%20former%20Microsoft%20colleague%20of%20his%20worked.%20After%20reaching%20out%2C%20Coachman%20said%20they%20recommended%20he%20focus%20on%20one%20specific%20role%20that%20they'd%20be%20willing%20to%20refer%20him%20for.%20The%20next%20day%2C%20Coachman%20received%20a%20call%20from%20a%20company%20recruiter.%20After%20the%20interview%20process%2C%20he%20received%20an%20offer%20and%20started%20working%20for%20the%20company%20in%20April.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFinding%20my%20next%20gig%20was%20100%25%20through%20my%20network%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECoachman%20said%20his%20pay%20is%20comparable%20to%20what%20he%20earned%20at%20Microsoft%2C%20and%20that%20the%20signing%20bonus%20helped%20make%20up%20for%20what%20he%20left%20behind%20in%20unvested%20stock.%20He%20said%20his%20travel%20is%20also%20now%20limited%20to%20no%20more%20than%20once%20a%20month%2C%20which%20was%20a%20big%20factor%20in%20his%20decision%20to%20accept%20the%20offer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20course%20of%20his%20roughly%20nine-month%20job%20search%2C%20Coachman%20said%20he%20applied%20to%20hundreds%20of%20jobs%20and%20received%20two%20offers%20%E2%80%94%20one%20for%20his%20current%20role%20and%20another%20from%20a%20startup%20he%20turned%20down%20due%20to%20concerns%20about%20job%20security.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20top%20advice%20for%20job%20seekers%3A%20build%20your%20network%20and%20lean%20on%20it.%20Rather%20than%20just%20connecting%20on%20LinkedIn%2C%20he%20said%2C%20it's%20better%20to%20have%20real%20conversations%20that%20help%20foster%20relationships.%20He%20said%20this%20could%20boost%20your%20chances%20of%20landing%20a%20referral%20down%20the%20road%20%E2%80%94%20giving%20your%20application%20the%20%26quot%3Bpersonal%20touch%26quot%3B%20it%20might%20need%20to%20get%20past%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-bad-resume-landed-12-job-interviews-in-eighty-days-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eapplicant%20tracking%20system%20scanners%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20real%20connections%20with%20people%20that%20I%20think%20make%20all%20the%20difference%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-layoffs-culture-change-employee-resigned-found-new-job-2025